caption: Wings are great
Ordered pickup from here tonight.  Got 4 types of wings, Cilantro lime, Guava buffalo, Enchilada, Elote.  All were fantastic and even tasted good after a 20 minute walk home!

Granero’s is the best place to have good food, listen to great music, and have a good time. The staff is always so kind and willing to help out their guests and the owner is always helping her guests to make sure they are having a good time! I definitely will be coming back here:)

What a great place in Logan Square! Has a nice urban vibe to it. You cannot go wrong with the drinks here. They’re amazing. Absolutely delicious, oh, and I must add, you have to try the guava wings, the Cuban sandwich and the fire roasted chicken. All definitely pleasing to the palate. Friendly service with a great staff. I’ll be returning.
This place is great! The food is delicious. The Elote wings, Buffalo Guava wings and Lola's Cuban sandwich are a must. Everything is delicious. The owner is awesome.  I will be back.

The food and drinks at Graneros is what keeps me coming back for more. Great place to hang out with friends in the Logan square neighborhood. The atmosphere is upbeat and inviting, they have a DJ on the weekend and during Sunday brunch. They have a good drink selection and the bartenders are great at there craft. Staff and owner are very friendly and the food is great. Check out there wings, Cuban sandwich and the empanadas are fantastic. The Sunday brunch is a great deal with bottomless mimosa to with endless amounts of food. The last time I was there I enjoyed 2 types of shrimp and wings as seen in the picture. I Definitely recommend checking them out and giving them some support during this time.

Granero is a great spot for food, drinks and hanging out in the Logan square neighborhood. The atmosphere is lively and inviting (they have a dj on weekend and during Sunday brunch). They have a good drink selection including delicious mojitos. Staff and owner are very friendly and the food is great. Check out their wings and Cuban sandwich special on Thursday’s (I believe). They also offer a bottomless mimosa brunch on Sunday’s as well which is a great deal. Definitely recommend checking them out and giving them some support during this time.
Food and drinks are excellent to go with the friendly staff.

Great food, faculty and prices! The atmosphere was awesome, staff was friendly and informative, the food was phenomenal in presentation, taste and the weekly specials made the experience that much more affordable & pleasant. I will definitely be returning to Granero!
The wings were great and the owner was very friendly and she even works the tables. She has a great attitude and was very attentive.
Great wings!

They never answer the phone. Don’t waste your time calling them. I had to drive over to place my order in person. I dialed the number when I was there and the phone rang. So it is a good number. Called them in the late afternoon several times on different days. They never answered. They are very rude for ignoring my calls. I guess they don’t want my business. I had the Thursday special- Lola’s Cuban sandwich. Not worth $10. I don’t want to even ask what the regular price is. Stay away from this place. We don’t need places like this in Logan Square. There are plenty of other places that will provide better customer service. Other businesses answer their phone calls. Came here before and sat at a table. Had to play music on my phone. They server said they had a problem with the audio system. The server also said that it is a reoccurring problem. Mezcal drinks are no good either.

This review is for the night scene. We came here for a graduation celebration. When we got here the line was pretty long. Once we got in, we had bottle service so we were seated on VIP. I was surprised at how small the dancefloor was, as the bar was pretty large and the seated area was nice. The place is well decorated. It was a mixed crowd. The DJ played some hip hop, rap. Reaggeton and some throwbacks. You should uber here as theres no parking. Genally enjoyed being here. Thank you.

Came with friends and was having a good time. Service was also great until an unannounced  event took place ( last minute event according to manager). Rating it a 1 because having a last minute event is not an excuse to disregard the other customers; especially when it comes to service and atmosphere. Manager said he couldn’t do much about it as it was out of his control.

Came here for my sisters birthday brunch and at first is was really good and food was good but then we were not told that there will be a soccer game event. They totally forgot about the people already in here and began overcrowding the place. They placed tables everywhere and the server was too focused on that and forgot about the clients. They said they would put the music back during half time and then at the end but to be realistic there were so many people there celebrating a special occasion that it didn’t make sense to anyone why they would do something like that. The manager wouldn’t do anything about it and many people ended walking out!
